
[1]statute-merchant

   STATUTE-MERCHANT, n. In English law, a bond of record pursuant to the
   Stat. 13 Edw. 1. acknowledged before one of the clerks of the
   statutes-merchant and the mayor or chief warden of London, or before
   certain persons appointed for the purpose; on which, if not paid at the
   day, an execution may be awarded against the body, lands and goods of
   the obligor.
